Recommendations & Next Steps
Strategic Recommendations
1. Rebalance Provider Workload
•	Adjust provider schedules to match peak encounter hours
•	Introduce cross coverage in high volume departments
•	Monitor provider utilization weekly
2. Improve Continuity of Care
•	Assign high utilizer patients to a primary provider
•	Use scheduling rules to prioritize continuity
•	Track UPC scores as a quality metric
3. Enhance Operational Visibility Develop a real time dashboard showing:
•	Encounters per provider
•	Encounter duration
•	Provider utilization
•	Continuity metrics
•	Peak demand windows
This supports proactive staffing decisions.
4. Standardize Documentation Workflows
•	Implement templates for common encounter types
•	Provide scribes or AI assisted documentation for high volume providers
•	Reduce after hours charting
5. Launch a High Utilizer Care Program
•	Identify top 5–10% of high utilizer patients
•	Assign care coordinators
•	Reduce unnecessary ED visits
•	Improve patient outcomes and operational efficiency
